definitions: not having arrived, happened, or been done by the expected time

examples.text: the rent was nearly three months overdue

shortDefinitions: not yet having arrived or been done

definitions: (of a woman) having gone beyond the expected time for a menstrual period

examples.text: I was already a week-and-a-half overdue

shortDefinitions: not having had menstrual period at expected time

definitions: (of a baby) not having been born by the expected time

examples.text: our daughter was six days overdue

shortDefinitions: not having been born at expected time

definitions: (of a library book) retained longer than the period allowed.
shortDefinitions: (of library book) retained longer than allowed

definitions: having been needed for some time
shortDefinitions: having been needed for some time

definitions: having deserved or needed something for some time

examples.text: she was overdue for some leave

shortDefinitions: having needed something for some time
